rmonMIB.contactinfo: postal: DKT A/S Fanoevej 6 DK-4060 Kirke Saaby Denmark email: info@dktcomega.com

rmonHistogramMode.name: rmonHistogramMode
rmonHistogramMode.description: Sets the mode of statistics capture. 0 = Rx only, 1 = Tx only, 2 = Sum of Rx and Tx.

rmonFlushAllCounter.name: rmonFlushAllCounter
rmonFlushAllCounter.description: Set to 1 for clearing all counters on all ports

rmonFlushPortCounter.name: rmonFlushPortCounter
rmonFlushPortCounter.description: Set to 1 for clearing all counters on a ports, input parameter is port number

rmonCPUPortGetInGoodOctetsLo.name: rmonCPUPortGetInGoodOctetsLo
rmonCPUPortGetInGoodOctetsLo.description: The sum of the lengths of all good Ethernet frames received, low size, that is frames that are not bad.

rmonCPUPortGetInGoodOctetsHi.name: rmonCPUPortGetInGoodOctetsHi
rmonCPUPortGetInGoodOctetsHi.description: The sum of the lengths of all good Ethernet frames received, high size, that is frames that are not bad.

rmonCPUPortGetInBadOctets.name: rmonCPUPortGetInBadOctets
rmonCPUPortGetInBadOctets.description: The sum of lengths of all bad Ethernet frames received not counting Preamble

rmonCPUPortGetOutFCSErr.name: rmonCPUPortGetOutFCSErr
rmonCPUPortGetOutFCSErr.description: The number of frames transmitted incorrectly due to an internal MAC transmit error, for example, bad CRC detected when the frame was read from memory

rmonCPUPortGetInUnicasts.name: rmonCPUPortGetInUnicasts
rmonCPUPortGetInUnicasts.description: The number of good frames received that have a Unicast destination address

rmonCPUPortGetDeferred.name: rmonCPUPortGetDeferred
rmonCPUPortGetDeferred.description: The total number of succesfully transmitted frames that were delayed because the medium was busy during the first attempt and when the frame was transmitted without any collisions (the counter is valid in half-duplex mode only)

rmonCPUPortGetInBroadcasts.name: rmonCPUPortGetInBroadcasts
rmonCPUPortGetInBroadcasts.description: The number of good frames received that have a Broadcast destination MAC address

rmonCPUPortGetInMulticasts.name: rmonCPUPortGetInMulticasts
rmonCPUPortGetInMulticasts.description: The number of good frames received that have a Multicast destination MAC address

rmonCPUPortGetOctets64.name: rmonCPUPortGetOctets64
rmonCPUPortGetOctets64.description: Total frames received (and/or transmitted) with a length of exactly 64 octets, including those with errors

rmonCPUPortGetOctets127.name: rmonCPUPortGetOctets127
rmonCPUPortGetOctets127.description: Total frames received (and/or transmitted) with a length of between 65 and 127 octets inclusive, including those with errors

rmonCPUPortGetOctets255.name: rmonCPUPortGetOctets255
rmonCPUPortGetOctets255.description: Total frames received (and/or transmitted) with a length of between 128 and 255 octets inclusive, including those with errors

rmonCPUPortGetOctets511.name: rmonCPUPortGetOctets511
rmonCPUPortGetOctets511.description: Total frames received (and/or transmitted) with a length of between 256 and 511 octets inclusive, including those with errors

rmonCPUPortGetOctets1023.name: rmonCPUPortGetOctets1023

rmonCPUPortGetOctetsMax.name: rmonCPUPortGetOctetsMax
rmonCPUPortGetOctetsMax.description: Total frames received (and/or transmitted) with a length of between 1024 and MaxSize octets inclusive, including those with errors

rmonCPUPortGetOutOctetsLo.name: rmonCPUPortGetOutOctetsLo
rmonCPUPortGetOutOctetsLo.description: The sum of all Ethernet frames sent from this MAC, low size, including flow control frames and partially frames transmitted due to collisions.

rmonCPUPortGetOutOctetsHi.name: rmonCPUPortGetOutOctetsHi
rmonCPUPortGetOutOctetsHi.description: The sum of all Ethernet frames sent from this MAC, high size, including flow control frames and partially frames transmitted due to collisions.

rmonCPUPortGetOutUnicasts.name: rmonCPUPortGetOutUnicasts
rmonCPUPortGetOutUnicasts.description: The number of frames sent that have a Unicast destination MAC address

rmonCPUPortGetExcessive.name: rmonCPUPortGetExcessive
rmonCPUPortGetExcessive.description: The number of frames dropped in the transmit MAC due to excessive collision condition. The counter is application in half-duplex mode only

rmonCPUPortGetOutMulticasts.description: The number of frames sent that have a Multicast destination MAC address

rmonCPUPortGetInPause.name: rmonCPUPortGetInPause
rmonCPUPortGetInPause.description: The number of flow control Pause frames received

rmonCPUPortGetMultiple.name: rmonCPUPortGetMultiple

rmonCPUPortGetUndersize.name: rmonCPUPortGetUndersize
rmonCPUPortGetUndersize.description: Total frames received with a length of less than 64 octets but with a valid FCS

rmonCPUPortGetFragments.name: rmonCPUPortGetFragments
rmonCPUPortGetFragments.description: Total frames received with a length of less than 64 octets and an invalid FCS

rmonCPUPortGetOversize.description: Total frames received with a length more than MaxSize octets but with a valid FCS

rmonCPUPortGetCollisions.description: The number of collision events seen by the MAC not including those counted in Late and Excessive

rmonCPUPortGetLate.name: rmonCPUPortGetLate
